export const helpMeteogramWindBarbs = () => `The wind is shown by wind barbs. The number of barb “flags”, in the arrow, indicates the speed with a precision of 2.5 km/h. For instance, an arrow with a single short flag indicate a speed between 0 and 2.5 km/h. If it has two short flags, it means a speed between 2.5 and 5 km/h. Two long flags mean a speed between 7.5 and 10 km/h. Four long flags mean a speed between 17.5 and 20 km/h, and so on. Alternatively, you can show the wind speed as a numerical value by going to the Settings from the top-left main menu.`;
